ike%20Canada%20and%20states%20like%20Georgia%20have%20become%20production%20hubs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELA's%20share%20of%20US%20film%20and%20TV%20jobs%20dropped%20to%2022%25%20in%20August%2C%20from%20about%2033%25%20two%20years%20earlier%2C%20according%20to%20new%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20figures%20analyzed%20by%20Patrick%20Adler%20and%20Taner%20Osman%20of%20Westwood%20Economics%20and%20Planning%20Associates%20Research.%20They%20also%20conducted%20research%20for%20a%20May%20Otis%20College%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.otis.edu%2Fabout%2Finitiatives%2Fdocuments%2Fotis-college-report-creative-economy-may-2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20creative%20economy%2C%20%26quot%3BDie%20Another%20Day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22656%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chart%20showing%20US%20entertainment%20employment%20trend%20data.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6718540b01ea6d83dee3517d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22462%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELA%20is%20losing%20TV%20and%20film%20jobs%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20US.%3Cp%3ESeasonally%20adjusted%20monthly%20employees%2C%20Motion%20Picture%20and%20Sound%20Recording%20Industries.%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20via%20Patrick%20Adler%20and%20Taner%20Osman%20on%20behalf%20of%20Otis%20College.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20isn't%20great%20for%20New%20York%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20No.%202%20entertainment%20job%20market%20in%20the%20US%20(after%20LA)%20also%20saw%20its%20share%20of%20film%20and%20TV%20jobs%20dip.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20country's%20portion%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20rose%20to%2069%25%20from%2054%25%20two%20years%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%20TV%20and%20film%20employment%20in%20the%20US%20was%20generally%20flat%20during%20the%20same%20period%20at%20about%20447%2C000%2C%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20a%2010%25%20decline%20during%20the%20writers'%20and%20actors'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsag-aftra-strike-end-tentative-agreement-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estrikes%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20largely%20shut%20down%20scripted%20production%20for%20much%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20really%20is%20a%20rise%20of%20the%20rest%2C%26quot%3B%20Adler%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20really%20didn't%20see%20this%20in%20the%20jobs%20data%20until%20a%20little%20bit%20after%20the%20strikes.%20This%20is%20where%20things%20are%20really%20starting%20to%20pick%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20few%20theories%20for%20the%20shift%2C%20and%20unsurprisingly%2C%20they%20boil%20down%20to%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20two%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EProducers%20are%20working%20with%20smaller%20budgets%20for%20shows%20and%20films%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftv-shows-bounce-back-new-rules-bring-pain-hollywood-points-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabor%20costs%20are%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20result%20of%20new%20union%20contracts%2C%20incentivizing%20filmmakers%20to%20leave%20LA%20for%20places%20in%20the%20US%20(as%20well%20as%20overseas)%20where%20costs%20are%20lower%20and%20financial%20perks%20are%20better.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELA's%20cost%20of%20living%20could%20be%20driving%20people%20to%20find%20work%20in%20other%20states%20where%20jobs%20have%20gotten%20more%20plentiful%2C%20thanks%20to%20generous%20film%20incentives%20in%20states%20like%20Georgia%20or%20new%20ones%20recently%20passed%20by%20states%20including%20Arizona%20and%20Kentucky.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIndustry%20advocates%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fentertainment-arts%2Fbusiness%2Fstory%2F2024-09-18%2Fcalifornias-film-industry-is-in-crisis-can-it-be-saved%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrying%20to%20boost%20the%20state's%20perks%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20lure%20more%20film%20and%20TV%20shoots%2C%20acknowledging%20the%20difficulty%20of%20competing%20with%20incentives%20offered%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFilmLA%20pointed%20to%20the%20importance%20of%20improving%20California's%20film%20incentive%20program%2C%20saying%20that%20one-fourth%20of%20TV%20drama%20shoot%20days%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%20were%20on%20incentive-supported%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCalifornia's%20film%20incentive%20is%20a%20proven%20jobs%20creator%20that%20studies%20show%20provides%20a%20net%20positive%20return%20on%20every%20allocated%20dollar%2C%26quot%3B%20FilmLA%20President%20Paul%20Audley%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20the%20program%20lacks%20is%20funding%20and%20eligibility%20criteria%20that%20reflect%20the%20outputs%20of%20the%20industry%20in%202024.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELA's%20entertainment%20industry%20isn't%20just%20Hollywood%2C%20however.%20The%20city%20also%20has%20a%20rich%20base%20of%20other%20entertainment%20sectors%20like%20gaming%20and%20social-media%20creation.%20Gaming%2C%20for%20example%2C%20was%20included%20in%20an%20employment%20category%20in%20Otis'%20May%20study%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bsoftware%20publishing%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20that%20rose%20149%25%20from%202013%20to%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20there's%20no%20single%20city%20that's%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20eclipsing%20LA's%20TV%20and%20film%20output.%20But%20if%20the%20trend%20away%20from%20LA%20continues%2C%20as%20it%20has%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20it%20could%20mean%20Hollywood%20won't%20be%20synonymous%20with%20TV%20and%20movies%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhollywood-losing-dominance-tv-movies-employment-chart-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729688341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671805e79b3250dbbce943b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhollywood-losing-dominance-tv-movies-employment-ch