%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAl%20Pacino%20as%20Michael%20Corleone%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Godfather%20Part%20II.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EParamount%20Pictures%2FIMDb%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20memoir%2C%20Puzo%20told%20him%3A%20%26quot%3B'It's%20crap%2C'%20he%20said%2C%20'I%20don't%20think%20the%20script%20is%20very%20good.%20But%20they%20gave%20it%20to%20me%20to%20give%20to%20you.%20I%20just%20want%20to%20tell%20you.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20reading%20the%20script%2C%20Pacino%20agreed%20with%20Puzo%20and%20thought%20he%20couldn't%20star%20in%20the%20film.%20Then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiane-keaton-nobody-wanted-al-pacino-cast-in-the-godfather-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParamount%3C%2Fa%3E%20approached%20him%20to%20raise%20his%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20kept%20coming%20to%20me%20with%20prices%2C%20and%20the%20prices%20kept%20going%20higher.%20First%20%24100%2C000.%20Then%20%24200%2C000.%20Then%20they%20got%20it%20to%20up%20to%20%24600%2C000.%20That%20was%20real%20money%20at%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20a%20producer%20called%20Pacino%20to%20his%20office%20to%20convince%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20he%20reached%20into%20his%20desk%2C%20and%20he%20pulled%20out%20a%20tin%20box.%20He%20said%20to%20me%3A%20'Al%2C%20what%20if%20I%20told%20you%20there's%20one%20million%20dollars%20in%20cash%20in%20that%20box%3F'%26quot%3B%20Pacino%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIt%20could%20have%20been%20a%20million%20bucks%20or%20packets%20of%20sugar%2C%20or%20it%20could%20have%20been%20empty.%20It%20was%20all%20out%20of%20my%20league.%20It%20was%20an%20abstraction.%20And%20it%20did%20not%20make%20one%20bit%20of%20difference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20Pacino%20made%20from%20the%20first%20film%20is%20not%20publicly%20known%2C%20but%20he%20wrote%20that%20he%20was%20broke%20and%20owed%20money%20after%20s