ions%20and%20the%20%242%20billion%20in%20annual%20aid%20to%20Pakistan%20were%20frozen.%20The%20US%20falsely%20claimed%20Davis%20was%20a%20diplomat%2C%20deserving%20immunity.%20Pakistan's%20investigation%20showed%20he%20was%20a%20Central%20Intelligence%20Agency%20(CIA)%20operative%20and%20therefore%20wasn't%20covered%20by%20diplomatic%20immunity.%20Initially%2C%20it%20refused%20to%20back%20down%20despite%20the%20political%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20after%20a%2050-day%20standoff%2C%20Davis%20was%20whisked%20back%20to%20the%20US%2C%20but%20not%20before%20%242.34%20million%20of%20blood%20money%20exchanged%20hands%2C%20reportedly%20compensating%20the%20victims'%20families.%20He%20later%20wrote%20about%20this%20cloak-and-dagger%20saga%20in%20his%202016%20book%C2%A0%3Ci%3EThe%20Contractor%3A%20How%20I%20Landed%20in%20Pakistan's%20Deadliest%20Jail%20and%20Then%20Escaped%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20revealing%20how%20the%20CIA%20operates%20when%20things%20get%20messy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECIA's%20Long%20Arms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Raymond%20Davis%20affair%20revealed%20how%20deeply%20the%20CIA%20was%20operating%20in%20Pakistan's%20backyard%2C%20raising%20public%20anger%20about%20America's%20covert%20meddling%20in%20a%20country%20it%20called%20an%20%26quot%3Bally%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20war%20on%20terror.%20The%20Pakistanis%20felt%20betrayed%20by%20their%20trusted%20ally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20brings%20us%20to%20the%20present%3A%20the%20CIA%2C%20the%20agency%20behind%20countless%20covert%20operations%20all%20around%20the%20world%2C%20lectures%20India%20on%20cooperating%20with%20Canada%20over%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar's%20assassination.%20It's%20as%20if%20the%20US%20forgot%20it's%20been%20running%20around%20the%20world%20in%20the%20shadows%20since%20the%20CIA's%20inception%20in%201947%2C%20toppling%20governments%2C%20orchestrating%20coups%2C%20and%20assassinating%20foreign%20leaders%E2%80%94all%20in%20the%20name%20of%20national%20interest.%20But%20let's%20not%20dwell%20on%20the%20hypocrisy%20or%20%26quot%3Bdouble%20standards%26quot%3B%2C%20as%20India's%20foreign%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20put%20it%20in%20a%20recent%20interview%20with%C2%A0%3Ci%3ENDTV%3C%2Fi%3E.%20He%20didn't%20hold%20back%20in%20calling%20out%20Canada's%20double%20standards%20and%20pointed%20out%20how%20it%20is%20quick%20to%20gather%20intel%20through%20its%20diplomats%20on%20foreign%20soil%20but%20becomes%20very%20protective%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20limiting%20similar%20activities%20by%20diplomats%20from%20other%20nations%20on%20its%20own%20turf.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20while%20Canada%20plays%20the%20victim%2C%20it%20conveniently%20turns%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20the%20unchecked%20privileges%20its%20own%20diplomats%20enjoy%20in%20India.%20Jaishankar%2C%20ever%20direct%2C%20put%20it%20plainly%3A%20%26quot%3BDouble%20standards%20is%20a%20very%20mild%20word%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%20His%20pointed%20remark%20wasn't%20just%20a%20dig%20at%20Canada's%20hypocrisy%20but%20also%20an%20indictment%20of%20the%20wider%20Western%20duplicity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%20the%20recent%20case%20of%20the%20US%20charging%20former%20Indian%20intelligence%20agent%20Vikas%20Yadav%20with%20being%20involved%20in%20a%20plot%20to%20assassinate%20Sikh%20separatist%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%20in%20New%20York.%20Now%2C%20imagine%20if%20the%20tables%20were%20turned.%20Would%20the%20US%20sit%20quietly%3F%20Absolutely%20not.%20By%20now%2C%20Washington%20would%20have%20launched%20a%20full-scale%20diplomatic%20offensive%20to%20bring%20its%20man%20home%2C%20just%20like%20it%20did%20in%20the%20above-mentioned%20case%20of%20Davis.%20And%20if%20this%20led%20to%20a%20potential%20diplomatic%20row%2C%20so%20be%20it.%20The%20hypocrisy%20is%20so%20obvious.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWest's%20Unquestioned%20Hypocrisy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20murky%20realm%20of%20espionage%2C%20agencies%20like%20the%20CIA%2C%20Mossad%20and%20MI6%20have%20always%20played%20by%20their%20own%20rules%2C%20causing%20diplomatic%20rifts%2C%20regime%20changes%20and%20the%20occasional%20assassinations.%20But%20when%20the%20tables%20turn%2C%20if%20at%20all%2C%20well%2C%20it's%20all%20about%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20international%20cooperation.%20I%20do%20not%20suggest%20the%20Indian%20spy%20agency%20RAW%20is%20doing%20what%20the%20likes%20of%20CIA%2C%20Mossad%20and%20MI6%20have%20been%20doing%20for%20decades%20without%20being%20questioned%20by%20anyone.%20The%20US%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20never%20lectured%20Israel%20for%20Mossad's%20countless%20extraterritorial%20activities%20overseas.%20India%20is%20cooperating%20with%20the%20US%20in%20the%20Vikas%20Yadav%20case.%20It%20wants%20to%20cooperate%20with%20Canada%20in%20its%20investigation%20of%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar's%20murder%20upon%20receipt%20of%20credible%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar's%20view%20isn't%20just%20an%20Indian%20perspective%E2%80%94countries%20across%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20and%20even%20some%20in%20the%20West%2C%20are%20getting%20increasingly%20fed%20up%20with%20the%20blatant%20foreign%20policy%20double%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Ajax'%20To%20'Condor'%2C%20CIA's%20Myriad%20Assassination%20Plots%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20government's%20own%20report%20on%20assassination%20plots%20involving%20foreign%20leaders%20reveals%20some%20shocking%20truths%20about%20the%20CIA's%20covert%20operations%20overseas.%20The%20report%C2%A0%3Ci%3EAlleged%20Assassination%20Plots%20Involving%20Foreign%20Leaders%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0wasn't%20fully%20declassified%20and%20released%20until%20July%2023%2C%202002.%20The%20report%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Church%20Committee%20report%2C%20investigated%20alleged%20CIA%20assassination%20plots%20against%20foreign%20leaders%2C%20including%20Cuba's%20Fidel%20Castro%20and%20Congo's%20Patrice%20Lumumba.%20The%20report%20also%20mentions%20other%20foreign%20leaders%20who%20were%20targeted%20for%20assassination%2C%20although%20their%20names%20were%20not%20disclosed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20White%20House's%20efforts%20to%20bury%20the%20report%2C%20the%20Church%20Committee%20conducted%20a%20thorough%20investigation%20into%20the%20CIA's%20assassination%20plots.%20It%20confirmed%20the%20CIA's%20involvement%20in%20these%20plots%20and%20recommended%20legislation%20to%20prohibit%20assassinations.%20The%20reports%20also%20raised%20important%20questions%20about%20the%20ethics%20and%20legality%20of%20targeted%20killings%2C%20which%20remain%20relevant%20today.%20And%20yet%2C%20the%20CIA%20often%20disregards%20its%20rule%20books%20and%20ethical%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20its%20notable%20plots%20were%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EOperation%20Ajax%20(1953)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Successfully%20overthrew%20Iranian%20Prime%20Minister%20Mohammad%20Mosaddegh%2C%20consolidating%20Shah%20Mohammad%20Reza%20Pahlavi's%20power.%20This%20was%20a%20joint%20operation%20between%20the%20CIA%20and%20Britain's%20MI6.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBay%20of%20Pigs%20Invasion%20(1961)%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFailed%20to%20overthrow%20Cuban%20leader%20Fidel%20Castro%2C%20resulting%20in%20embarrassment%20to%20the%20US%20and%20loss%20of%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EOperation%20Condor%20(1970s-1980s)%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Supported%20Latin%20American%20dictatorships%20in%20eliminating%20leftist%20opposition%2C%20leading%20to%20human%20rights%20abuses.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20more%20recent%20times%2C%20the%20CIA's%20extraterritorial%20actions%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20especially%20during%20the%20%E2%80%98War%20on%20Terror'%2C%20have%20had%20long-term%20destabilising%20effects.%20US%20drone%20strikes%2C%20covert%20actions%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20Yemen%20and%20Somalia%20and%20operations%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%20have%20sometimes%20led%20to%20increased%20radicalisation.%20While%20these%20operations%20are%20aimed%20at%20counterterrorism%2C%20the%20resulting%20instability%20often%20fuels%20new%20cycles%20of%20violence%20and%20anti-American%20sentiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMossad's%20Misdemeanours%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20experts%20in%20the%20West%20are%20bracing%20for%20a%20fiery%20Israeli%20strike%20on%20Iran%20in%20response%20to%20Tehran's%20October%201%20missile%20attack.%20But%20here's%20the%20catch%E2%80%94it%20may%20not%20come%20from%20the%20skies%20at%20all.%20Instead%20of%20sending%20jets%20and%20missiles%2C%20Israel%20could%20very%20well%20stick%20to%20its%20trusted%20playbook%3A%20cyberattacks%20or%20political%20assassinations.%20After%20all%2C%20these%20methods%20have%20proven%20highly%20effective%20in%20the%20past%2C%20often%20executed%20with%20the%20help%20of%20local%20assets%20within%20Iran.%20So%2C%20while%20everyone%20waits%20for%20a%20military%20show%20of%20force%2C%20Israel%20might%20be%20quietly%20sharpening%20its%20digital%20knives%20or%20preparing%20for%20another%20covert%20strike%20that%20leaves%20no%20fingerprints%20but%20sends%20a%20very%20loud%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20widely%20believed%2C%20and%20not%20disputed%20by%20Israel%2C%20that%20Mossad%20has%20been%20actively%20involved%20in%20covert%20operations%20inside%20Iran%20for%20years%2C%20particularly%20targeting%20Iran's%20nuclear%20programme.%20One%20might%20recall%20the%20cyberattack%20using%20the%20Stuxnet%20virus%2C%20which%20disrupted%20uranium%20enrichment%20in%202010.%20In%202018%2C%20Mossad%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20stolen%2055%2C000%20pages%20of%20documents%20and%20183%20CDs%20from%20Iran's%20nuclear%20archives%2C%20revealing%20the%20country's%20nuclear%20programme%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Mossad's%20most%20high-profile%20and%20controversial%20actions%20have%20been%20the%20assassinations%20of%20Iranian%20nuclear%20scientists.%20These%20operations%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20Israeli%20strategy%20to%20delay%20or%20dismantle%20Iran's%20nuclear%20capabilities%2C%20which%20Israel%20sees%20as%20an%20existential%20threat.%20Between%202010%20and%202012%2C%20at%20least%20five%20Iranian%20nuclear%20scientists%20were%20assassinated%20in%20Tehran%20in%20a%20series%20of%20precision%20attacks%20that%20many%20attributed%20to%20Mossad.%20Israel%20has%20not%20commented%20on%20them.%20The%20most%20notable%20method%20involved%20motorcyclists%20attaching%20magnetic%20bombs%20to%20the%20victims'%20cars%20during%20busy%20commutes.%20The%20victims%20included%20Majid%20Shahriari%2C%20a%20key%20figure%20in%20Iran's%20nuclear%20research%2C%20and%20Mostafa%20Ahmadi%20Roshan%2C%20a%20prominent%20scientist%20at%20Iran's%20Natanz%20nuclear%20facility.%20These%20killings%20sent%20shockwaves%20through%20Iran's%20scientific%20community%2C%20severely%20damaging%20its%20nuclear%20programme%20and%20provoking%20outrage%20from%20Tehran%2C%20which%20accused%20Israel%20and%20the%20West%20of%20orchestrating%20the%20murders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Strikes%20On%20Iran's%20Nuclear%20Ambitions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20striking%20assassination%20occurred%20in%202020%20when%20Mohsen%20Fakhrizadeh%2C%20considered%20the%20father%20of%20Iran's%20nuclear%20weapons%20programme%2C%20was%20killed%20in%20a%20highly%20sophisticated%20operation.%20Reports%20suggested%20the%20use%20of%20a%20satellite-controlled%20machine%20gun%20to%20eliminate%20Fakhrizadeh%20near%20Tehran.%20This%20assassination%20was%20a%20major%20blow%20to%20Iran's%20nuclear%20ambitions.%20Mossad's%20operations%20inside%20Iran%20demonstrate%20the%20agency's%20deep%20penetration%20into%20the%20country%20and%20its%20relentless%20efforts%20to%20undermine%20Iran's%20nuclear%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIranian%20secret%20agents%20have%20also%20been%20active%20against%20Israel%2C%20with%20the%20Israeli%20government%20successfully%20foiling%20Iranian%20plots%20to%20assassinate%20Israelis%20in%20Israel%2C%20Cyprus%20and%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMI6%20And%20Its%20Legacy%20Spy%20Network%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20as%20the%20original%20colonial%20power%2C%20practically%20wrote%20the%20book%20on%20covert%20operations.%20MI6%2C%20founded%20in%201909%20as%20the%20Empire's%20main%20Secret%20Intelligence%20Service%2C%20was%20tasked%20with%20protecting%20British%20interests%20worldwide%E2%80%94sometimes%20by%20any%20means%20necessary.%20One%20of%20its%20most%20infamous%20escapades%20was%20its%20role%20in%20the%201953%20coup%20against%20Iran's%20Prime%20Minister%20Mohammad%20Mossadegh%2C%20a%20man%20who%20dared%20to%20nationalise%20Iran's%20oil%2C%20threatening%20Britain's%20golden%20pipeline.%20As%20mentioned%20above%2C%20the%20MI6%20teamed%20up%20with%20the%20CIA%20for%20Operation%20Ajax%2C%20toppling%20Mossadegh%20and%20reinstalling%20the%20Shah%2C%20whose%20authoritarian%20reign%20would%20last%20until%20the%201979%20revolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20more%20recent%20times%2C%20especially%20during%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20MI6%20found%20itself%20embroiled%20in%20another%20scandal%2C%20this%20time%20involving%20Libya.%20Partnering%20again%20with%20the%20CIA%2C%20MI6%20was%20accused%20of%20helping%20to%20render%20Libyan%20dissidents%20back%20to%20Gaddafi's%20regime%2C%20where%20they%20were%20tortured.%20The%20most%20prominent%20case%20was%20that%20of%20Abdel%20Hakim%20Belhaj%2C%20an%20opposition%20leader%20kidnapped%20and%20sent%20to%20Libya%20allegedly%20with%20MI6's%20help.%20After%20years%20of%20legal%20battles%2C%20Belhaj%20won%20an%20apology%20from%20Prime%20Minister%20Theresa%20May%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia's%20RAW%20Power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20Research%20and%20Analysis%20Wing%20(RAW)%20was%20established%20in%201968%20as%20the%20nation's%20primary%20external%20intelligence%20agency.%20While%20RAW%20has%20gained%20significant%20prominence%20within%20the%20global%20intelligence%20community%2C%20its%20capabilities%20still%20trail%20behind%20those%20of%20the%20CIA%2C%20Mossad%2C%20and%20MI6.%20With%20a%20reported%20budget%20of%20around%20%24700%20million%2C%20RAW%20operates%20on%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20resources%20available%20to%20the%20CIA%2C%20whose%20budget%20hovers%20between%20%2418-20%20billion.%20Its%20main%20mandate%20is%20national%20security%2C%20with%20a%20sharp%20focus%20on%20counterterrorism%E2%80%94disrupting%20terror%20outfits%2C%20cutting%20off%20funding%20to%20extremists%2C%20and%20monitoring%20state%20enemies%20abroad.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EContrary%20to%20popular%20belief%2C%20RAW%20does%20not%20operate%20with%20unchecked%20power.%20Its%20operations%20are%20governed%20by%20strict%20directives%20from%20the%20Indian%20government%20and%2C%20at%20least%20on%20paper%2C%20must%20adhere%20to%20Indian%20laws.%20While%20RAW%20plays%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20safeguarding%20the%20nation%2C%20it%20is%20by%20no%20means%20a%20rogue%20agency%3B%20it%20works%20within%20the%20limits%20of%20its%20mandate%2C%20with%20each%20mission%20requiring%20government%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20CIA's%20colossal%20resources%20and%20Mossad's%20precision%20strikes%20to%20MI6's%20legacy%20of%20colonial%20espionage%20and%20RAW's%20rising%20influence%2C%20these%20agencies%20navigate%20the%20murky%20waters%20of%20international%20politics%20and%C2%A0diplomacy.%C2%A0Yet%2C%20they%20remain%20indispensable%20tools%20of%20statecraft%20in%20an%20increasingly%20complex%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729679700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fgtq0m7hg_spy_625x3