ng%20Korean%20words%20and%20food%20traditions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Neha%20Vashist%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fhindi%2Fanushka-sen-as-an-actor-you-are-just-hungry-for-an-opportunity-exclusive%2Farticleshow%2F114503365.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chief%20Justice's%20Big%20Move%20In%20Marital%20Rape%20Case%20--%20And%20Lawyer's%20Legacy%20Remark%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20will%20no%20longer%20hear%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20immunity%20granted%20to%20husbands%20in%20marital%20rape%20cases.%20The%20decision%20was%20taken%20because%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20is%20due%20to%20retire%20on%20November%2010%20and%20the%20bench%2C%20also%20comprising%20Justice%20JB%20Pardiwala%20and%20Justice%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20complete%20hearing%20the%20submissions%20and%20give%20a%20verdict%20before%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Justice-led%20bench%20adjourned%20the%20matter%20for%20four%20weeks.%20A%20new%20bench%20will%20hear%20the%20matter%20after%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%20today%2C%20lawyers%20representing%20several%20parties%20said%20they%20would%20take%20time%20to%20make%20their%20submissions%20in%20the%20matter.%C2%A0Senior%20Advocate%20Sankarnarayanan%20said%20he%20would%20take%20at%20least%20a%20day%20to%20complete%20his%20submissions.%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20said%20he%20would%20take%20a%20day%20too.%20So%20did%20Senior%20Advocate%20Rakesh%20Dwivedi.%20Maninder%20Singh%2C%20Arvind%20Datar%20and%20Indira%20Jaising%20are%20the%20other%20lawyers%20appearing%20in%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThen%20this%20can%20be%20deferred%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20heard%20submissions%20by%20Ms%20Nundy.%20Mr%20Gopal%20Sankarnarayan%20says%20he%20will%20require%20one%20day.%20This%20will%20be%20followed%20by%20submissions%20by%20Senior%20Advocate%20Jaising%20and%20other%20counsels%20will%20take%20a%20day%20each.%20The%20above%20estimates%20show%20that%20arguments%20will%20be%20heard%20for%20intervenors%2C%20rape%20accused%20and%20respondents.%20Hence%20it%20will%20not%20be%20possible%20to%20complete%20the%20hearing%20in%20the%20foreseeable%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20ordering%20the%20matter%20to%20be%20relisted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20Advocate%20Karuna%20Nundy%2C%20appearing%20for%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYour%20(Chief%20Justice)%20legacy%20would%20warrant%20this%20case%20to%20be%20heard%20for%20the%20millions%20of%20women.%26quot%3B%C2%A0To%20this%2C%20the%20Solicitor%20General%20responded%2C%20%26quot%3BYour%20lordship's%20legacy%20will%20be%20remembered%20and%20this%20statement%20need%20not%20be%20made.%26quot%3B%C2%A0The%20Chief%20Justice%20noted%20that%20all%20parties%20have%20to%20make%20arguments%20and%20directed%20that%20the%20matter%20be%20listed%20after%20four%20weeks.%C2%A0The%20hearing%20in%20the%20matter%20started%20on%20October%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20newly-implemented%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20grants%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20to%20a%20husband%20for%20rape%20if%20his%20wife%20is%20not%20a%20minor.%20Under%20the%20new%20law%2C%20exception%202%20to%20Section%2063%20(rape)%20says%20%26quot%3Bsexual%20intercourse%20or%20sexual%20acts%20by%20a%20man%20with%20his%20own%20wife%2C%20the%20wife%20not%20being%20under%20eighteen%20years%20of%20age%2C%20is%20not%20rape%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20has%20told%20the%20court%20that%20there%20is%20no%20need%20to%20criminalise%20marital%20rape%20and%20that%20it%20is%20not%20within%20the%20court's%20purview%20to%20take%20this%20decision.%20The%20government%20has%20said%20that%20the%20marital%20rape%20issue%20is%20more%20a%20social%20issue%20than%20a%20legal%20one%20as%20it%20will%20have%20a%20direct%20impact%20on%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Parliament%2C%20the%20Centre%20has%20argued%2C%20has%20provided%20several%20measures%20to%20protect%20the%20consent%20of%20a%20married%20woman%20within%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sexual%20aspect%2C%20it%20said%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20many%20aspects%20of%20the%20relationship%20between%20a%20husband%20and%20wife%20on%20which%20the%20foundation%20of%20their%20marriage%20rests.%20If%20the%20legislature%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage%20is%20essential%2C%20it%20would%20not%20be%20appropriate%20for%20the%20court%20to%20strike%20down%20the%20exception%2C%20the%20Centre%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729678260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fotj21qvg_justice-dy-chandrachud_625x300_03_October_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmarital-rape-case-chief-justice-dy-chandrachud-chief-justices-big-move-in-marital-rape-case-and-lawyers-legacy-remark-6855060%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20will%20no%20longer%20hear%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20immunity%20granted%20to%20husbands%20in%20marital%20rape%20cases%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmarital-rape-case-chief-justice-dy-chandrachud-chief-justices-big-move-in-marital-rape-case-and-lawyers-legacy-remark-6855060%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Mad%20Max%3A%20Fury%20Road%E2%80%99%20Lenser%20John%20Seale%20to%20Deliver%20Masterclass%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20IFFI%20Sets%20Australia%20as%20Country%20of%20Focus%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729677989000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FMCDMAMA_EC185.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%